<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="508" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,871,1222]" pageId="1" pageNumber="508">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,943,969]" pageId="1" pageNumber="508">Remarks.</emphasis>
The specimens that we have examined closely match the original description provided by 
<bibRefCitation author="Miyamoto, S." pageId="1" pageNumber="508" pagination="137 - 150" refId="ref7684" refString="Miyamoto, S. (1964) Veliidae of the Ryukyus (Hemiptera, Heteroptera). Kontyu, 32 (1), 137 - 150." type="journal article" year="1964">Miyamoto (1964)</bibRefCitation>
. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Miyamoto" authorityYear="1964" box="[241,466,979,1005]" class="Insecta" family="Veliidae" genus="Pseudovelia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="508" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="takarai">
<emphasis box="[241,466,979,1005]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="508">Pseudovelia takarai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be distinguished by its relatively dark ground color (
<figureCitation box="[1114,1183,979,1005]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–6" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[253,1330,191,1911]" captionTargetId="figure-18@3.[241,1345,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1–6. Habitus of Pseudovelia spp. (males). 1. P. buccula Andersen, 1983; 2. P. takarai Miyamoto, 1964; 3. P. curvisetae sp. nov.; 4. P. plauta sp. nov.; 5. P. shaanxiensis sp. nov.; 6. P. zhengi sp. nov. Scale 1.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6816717" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6816717/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="508">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[1196,1210,979,1005]" captionStart="FIGURES 7–12" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[271,1323,194,1901]" captionTargetId="figure-21@4.[254,1333,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 7–12. Habitus of Pseudovelia spp. (apterous females). 7. P. buccula Andersen, 1983; 8. P. takarai Miyamoto, 1964; 9. P. curvisetae sp. nov.; 10. P. plauta sp. nov.; 11. P. shaanxiensis sp. nov.; 12. P. zhengi sp. nov. Scale 1.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6816721" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6816721/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="508">8</figureCitation>
) and a short, nearly globular hind tarsal segment I (
<figureCitation box="[509,595,1015,1041]" captionStart="FIGURES 29–34" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1043,1067]" captionTargetBox="[162,1423,189,1009]" captionTargetId="figure-21@8.[151,1436,181,1019]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 29–34. Hind legs of Pseudovelia spp. (males). 29. P. buccula Andersen, 1983; 30. P. takarai Miyamoto, 1964; 31. P. curvisetae sp. nov.; 32. P. plauta sp. nov.; 33. P. shaanxiensis sp. nov.; 34. P. zhengi sp. nov. Scale 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6816733" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6816733/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="508">Fig. 30</figureCitation>
). Abdominal segment VIII (
<figureCitation box="[915,1010,1015,1041]" captionStart="FIGURES 35–40" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1771,1795]" captionTargetBox="[174,1415,226,1669]" captionTargetId="figure-18@9.[151,1436,211,1681]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 35–40. Abdominal segment VIII of Pseudovelia spp. (males). 35. P. buccula Andersen, 1983; 36. P. takarai Miyamoto, 1964; 37. P. curvisetae sp. nov.; 38. P. plauta sp. nov.; 39. P. shaanxiensis sp. nov.; 40. P. zhengi sp. nov. Scale 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6816737" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6816737/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="508">Figs. 36</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[1023,1054,1015,1041]" captionStart="FIGURES 41–46" captionStartId="10.[151,264,1813,1837]" captionTargetBox="[151,1427,216,1720]" captionTargetId="figure-21@10.[151,1436,211,1738]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 41–46. Abdominal segment VIII of Pseudovelia spp. (males). 41. P. buccula Andersen, 1983; 42. P. takarai Miyamoto, 1964; 43. P. curvisetae sp. nov.; 44. P. plauta sp. nov.; 45. P. shaanxiensis sp. nov.; 46. P. zhengi sp. nov. Scale 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6816739" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6816739/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="508">42</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[1067,1097,1015,1041]" captionStart="FIGURES 47–52" captionStartId="11.[151,264,1860,1884]" captionTargetBox="[173,1410,201,1790]" captionTargetId="figure-18@11.[151,1436,181,1808]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURES 47–52. Abdominal segment VIII of Pseudovelia spp. (males). 47. P. buccula Andersen, 1983; 48. P. takarai Miyamoto, 1964; 49. P. curvisetae sp. nov.; 50. P. plauta sp. nov.; 51. P. shaanxiensis sp. nov.; 52. P. zhengi sp. nov. Scale 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6816743" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6816743/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="508">48</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[1111,1140,1015,1042]" captionStart="FIGURES 53–58" captionStartId="12.[151,264,1862,1886]" captionTargetBox="[154,1433,182,1778]" captionTargetId="figure-21@12.[151,1436,181,1795]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES 53–58. Abdominal segment VIII of Pseudovelia spp. (males). 53. P. buccula Andersen, 1983; 54. P. takarai Miyamoto, 1964; 55. P. curvisetae sp. nov.; 56. P. plauta sp. nov.; 57. P. shaanxiensis sp. nov.; 58. P. zhengi sp. nov. Scale 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6816745" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6816745/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="508">54</figureCitation>
) of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Miyamoto" authorityYear="1964" box="[1188,1298,1015,1041]" class="Insecta" family="Veliidae" genus="Pseudovelia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="508" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="takarai">
<emphasis box="[1188,1298,1015,1041]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="508">P. takarai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has a large, oval-like depression; the lateral margin of the depression has two tufts of setae and dense, suberect, black hairs; the longitudinal midline of the depression bears two rows of small bristles. The pygophore (
<figureCitation box="[1122,1202,1087,1113]" captionStart="FIGURES 59–64" captionStartId="13.[151,264,1165,1189]" captionTargetBox="[234,1369,196,1128]" captionTargetId="figure-18@13.[205,1381,181,1141]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURES 59–64. Pygophore of Pseudovelia spp. (males). 59. P. buccula Andersen, 1983; 60. P. takarai Miyamoto, 1964; 61. P. curvisetae sp. nov.; 62. P. plauta sp. nov.; 63. P. shaanxiensis sp. nov.; 64. P. zhengi sp. nov. Scale 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6816747" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6816747/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="508">Fig. 60</figureCitation>
) is slightly narrowed in the middle; the anterior margin has a pair of dense, long bristles. Based on current collection data, this species might have a wide distribution in the Oriental regions. This is a new record for 
<collectingCountry box="[1039,1110,1159,1185]" name="China" pageId="1" pageNumber="508">China</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
